<br>
   You're comparing apples and oranges.  This is a DoT spell, not DD.  They have almost exactly the same damage/mana ratio as far as that goes.  You can't realistically compare DPS of a dot vs DD as they arn't used for the same thing.  Also, at 55, you don't have access to shock of fiery blades.  <br>
<br>
  Wrath has a significantly better damage/mana ratio than Char and Shock of Swords however.  Not to mention again as the poster above, the aggro issue.  Chain nuking a mob for 1000+ is going to give you a one way ticket to your bind point.  Most top end encounter mobs hate lists don't work on total hate, but rather total hate/some time frame.  I consistently open fights with Wrath simply for it's efficiency.  It's also all or nothing, much like enchanter nukes.  If they catch anything, they catch the full 800, unlike char/SoS/sofb's partial resists.  I don't think I've ever not had it up for any fight. <br>
<br>
  Also, go toss SoFB around in zones like skyfire and CT.  There are mobs that are almost completley resistant to fire nukes there, taking you down to your option of Shock of Steel, where Wrath has a better damage/mana ratio as well.  <br>
<br>
  There are definatley a ton of advantages to this, and it is a great addition to the mage class <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
